   <titles>
      <title>The Graph of a Dis-Continuous Function</title>
   </titles>
   <body>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>Whenever the domain of a function <math>
                     <latex>f\from J\to \RNr</latex>
                  </math> is a interval, jumps in the graph of <math>
                     <latex>f</latex>
                  </math> correspond to places of discontinuity of <math>
                     <latex>f</latex>
                  </math>.</para.body>
            </para>
            <media type="image" active="0" inline="0">
               <img src="ims/ContDisContGraph.png"/>
            </media>
            <para>
               <para.body>On the left, a continuous function: its graph makes no jumps. On the right, a function with a discontinuity: its graph makes a vertical jump.</para.body>
            </para>
         </block.body>
      </block>
   </body>
